      "date": "2014-10-25 01:20:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Yawei,\n\nI am not sure other bits has race problems. I guess nrs_throttling is different because only this bit can be changed in a timer interrupt.\n\nWe've confirmed removing the lock when changing nrs_throttling fixes the deadlock problem. But you are right, there might be race. It won't cause severe problem but might cause inaccurate RPC rate. Do you think it is proper to change the bit to a atomic type. I.e. 1) when policy want to throttle RPC rate, it increases the atomi value 2) and in the timer interrupt, the value is decreased. I am not sure about the performance, please advise.\n\nThank you!",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
